subject:

RAIN AND SHINE: BOTH REAL (read 2 Cor. 6:3-13)
===================================================================
verse:

Sorrowful, yet always rejoicing; poor, yet making many rich;
having nothing, and yet possessing everything. (2 Cor. 6:10)

===================================================================
reflection:

In the verse for today, Paul acknowledged the existence of
sorrow and at the same time identified the reason for
rejoicing: Christ Jesus, who redeemed us and rose victorious
over all sorrow and every problem. Alongside the rain we
have the very real Son. If we have the Son, we can overcome
mentally and Spiritually the storms of life.

===================================================================
prayer:

Lord Jesus, You are the victorious Son who has redeemed us
from every sorrow and trial. In the storms of life, help me
remember that with You, I can overcome all challenges
mentally and spiritually. Fill my heart with joy and peace,
even amid difficulties, and strengthen my faith to trust in
Your unfailing love. May Your victory be my hope and my
constant source of strength. Amen. (AI)

===================================================================
